Mix together sour cream, flour, brown sugar, and egg. Stir until well blended. Spoon half the mixture into crust. Top with 1 cup blueberry pie filling. Spoon remaining sour cream mixture over pie filling. Bake at 400 F for 30 minutes. Cool and place in refrigerator to chill. Garnish with a tablespoon of pie filling on top of each slice prior to serving.